562
00:47:19,657 --> 00:47:23,247
Oh, should I?

563
00:47:37,757 --> 00:47:41,727
What do you think about Dr. Oh?

564
00:47:44,007 --> 00:47:46,627
Dr. Oh...

565
00:47:46,627 --> 00:47:49,427
At first, I thought she was a quack with only a sharp hand.

566
00:47:49,427 --> 00:47:52,597
But after seeing her awhile, she tries hard, too,

567
00:47:52,597 --> 00:47:56,107
and because I think she is slowly becoming a real doctor,

568
00:47:56,107 --> 00:47:58,627
she's also cute.

569
00:48:00,627 --> 00:48:05,587
When I keep looking at her, I get reminded of Jae Hee sometimes.

570
00:48:05,587 --> 00:48:09,457
Does Jae Hee look like Dr. Oh?

571
00:48:09,457 --> 00:48:10,967
That's not it.

572
00:48:10,967 --> 00:48:15,407
Just, I wish Jae Hee would be more like Quack.

573
00:48:15,407 --> 00:48:17,267
As a doctor.

574
00:48:17,267 --> 00:48:21,297
How is Dr. Oh as a woman?

575
00:48:22,507 --> 00:48:28,697
Hey you... Do you think I like Quack or something?

576
00:48:28,697 --> 00:48:31,447
It can be the opposite.

577
00:48:31,447 --> 00:48:36,837
Wait, by chance, are you concerned Quack would like me?

578
00:48:38,397 --> 00:48:42,097
My goodness... This person is so...

579
00:48:44,577 --> 00:48:46,857
Oh, this is...

580
00:48:48,917 --> 00:48:54,027
This person was worried that I would like you.

581
00:48:54,027 --> 00:48:56,787
How can you pick up someone else's phone?

582
00:48:56,787 --> 00:48:59,027
You kept calling so I picked it up, thinking it might be urgent.

583
00:48:59,027 --> 00:49:01,197
Did you perhaps say you like me over the phone?

584
00:49:01,197 --> 00:49:04,117
Stop sprouting nonsense.

585
00:49:06,227 --> 00:49:07,657
Stop and please eat.

586
00:49:07,657 --> 00:49:11,487
Hey, Quack. Honestly, we just can't be.

587
00:49:12,327 --> 00:49:15,077
I'm sorry when your beloved man is here, but

588
00:49:15,077 --> 00:49:18,117
the people I hate the most are ones with a bad temper.

589
00:49:18,117 --> 00:49:22,057
On top of that, your violence, vanity, and whoa...

590
00:49:22,057 --> 00:49:25,587
Hey, did I say I like you?

591
00:49:26,867 --> 00:49:29,987
I was trying to act kindly because I took pity on you for getting kicked out of the hospital. You're seriously...

592
00:49:29,987 --> 00:49:31,397
Relax.

593
00:49:31,397 --> 00:49:33,127
How can I relax?

594
00:49:33,127 --> 00:49:37,837
I called you because I thought you weren't even eating properly, but your words are too harsh.

595
00:49:37,837 --> 00:49:40,917
The one being too harsh is you, Soo Hyeon.

596
00:49:40,917 --> 00:49:44,617
- Stop.
- How am I being too harsh?

597
00:49:51,017 --> 00:49:53,357
I'll go.

598
00:50:04,177 --> 00:50:06,547
You were too harsh.

599
00:50:06,547 --> 00:50:09,087
It's okay.

600
00:50:09,087 --> 00:50:11,827
You got along well at the hospital.

601
00:50:11,827 --> 00:50:14,647
How did you know I liked curry?

602
00:50:14,647 --> 00:50:18,817
I'm curious, too. How did Dr. Oh know that?

603
00:50:19,747 --> 00:50:22,007
Quack did?

604
00:50:23,897 --> 00:50:26,477
Forget it.  Just eat.

605
00:50:37,827 --> 00:50:39,577
Are you okay?

606
00:50:39,577 --> 00:50:43,297
What a jerk! Can he disregard a person's good will like this?

607
00:50:43,297 --> 00:50:45,787
- Do you, by chance, like him?
- What?

608
00:50:45,787 --> 00:50:47,867
It's not like Dr. Park has acted like that for only a day or two.

609
00:50:47,867 --> 00:50:49,537
It's something you could've just laughed over.

610
00:50:49,537 --> 00:50:53,867
So, are you saying I'm overreacting?

611
00:50:53,867 --> 00:50:55,937
First off, calm down a bit.

612
00:50:57,047 --> 00:51:00,567
I get it, so can you leave me alone for a bit?

613
00:51:00,567 --> 00:51:03,747
Okay. Once you calm down a little, come downstairs.

614
00:51:11,137 --> 00:51:13,507
Jerk!

615
00:51:35,727 --> 00:51:38,647
I guess there won't be a reason to see each other in the future.

616
00:51:38,647 --> 00:51:40,777
I guess so.

617
00:51:48,137 --> 00:51:50,347
They are my parents.

618
00:51:53,927 --> 00:51:56,957
Are your parents in the US?

619
00:51:56,957 --> 00:51:59,817
You can say so.

620
00:51:59,817 --> 00:52:01,927
You must be sad since you can't see them often.

621
00:52:01,927 --> 00:52:04,397
It's not so bad for me compared to others.

622
00:52:04,397 --> 00:52:07,347
In North Korea, Dr. Park's father was...

